All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    Circle
    Child class of Figure that creates the circles of the corresponding tiles.
    Color
    Class used to define colors of figures and the backgrounds of tiles.
    Coordinate
    Class that creates the coordinates that each region of the mosaic has.
    Figure
    Abstract class that represents the figure of the tile, that is a circle or a rectangle, which are its children classes.
    Luminosity
    Interface that manages the luminosity changes of the colors of tiles, regions and mosaics.
    Mosaic
    Class that creates the Mosaic, the final structure which is made of rectangular regions.
    MosaicProject
    Class from which we receive the instructions and the required information to carry out the creation of our mosaic and all its components.
    Rectangle
    Child class of Figure that creates the rectangles of the corresponding tiles.
    Tile
    Class that creates the tiles, the simplest structure of the mosaic.
    TileOutOfBoundsException
    Class that creates the TileOutOfBoundsException which inherits from class Exception and is thrown when a tile is out of bounds of the mosaic.
